				<div class="box related">
			<h3>Sources</h3>
			
<p>USDA, ‘Ghana poultry report: Annual’, <i>GAIN Report</i> No. 1303, 6 August 2013</p><p>
<a href="http://gain.fas.usda.gov/Recent%20GAIN%20Publications/Ghana%20Poultry%20Report%20Annual_Accra_Ghana_8-6-2013.pdf" target="_self">http://gain.fas.usda.gov/Recent%20GAIN%20Publications/Ghana%20Poultry%20...</a></p>		</div>
		
		
				<div class="box">
			<h3>Editorial comment</h3>
			<p>Since February 2013, as part of efforts to mitigate the impact of poultry product imports on local poultry producers, the Ghanaian Ministry of Food and Agriculture has been intensifying its engagement with the Ghana Poultry Farmers Association and other key stakeholders along the value chain. This engagement includes plans to rapidly establish a poultry council to regulate the activities of operators in the industry. The aim is to identify ways of enhancing the competitiveness of local poultry producers and get to grips with the market consequences of increased imports of poultry products.</p><p>On the production side, this involves addressing the problem of high feed costs. One approach is by promoting a more integrated local supply chain, including by supporting local production of soybeans and increasing access to local maize production for feed use. Local poultry producers also believe that more can be done to improve the efficiency of certain components of the poultry value chain (e.g. by reducing the costs of day-old chicks either by improving the efficiency of the hatchery or facilitating the efficient supply of imported day-old-chicks).</p><p>On the trade policy side, the Ghanaian government is looking to reform the administration of the import permit system in order to enhance the monitoring of both quantity and quality of imported poultry products. Most local poultry sector stakeholders believe that local poultry products are of a superior quality to imported poultry meat, which contains a higher percentage of brine and which, when defrosted, yields a far lower volume of poultry meat than the nominal weight.</p>
		</div>
		
